# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
First, if x,y is reachable, then y,x is reachable. So only take care the case x <= y.>
The end point, if x = 1, then it surely is true, since you can use 1,1 and x,y -> x, 2y to reach 1,k until k is not smaller than y, then use x,y -> x, y-x to reach the final value.
if x = y and x is odd number and not 1, then it is a false case. since x, x and only come from x,0 and x,2x. And x,2x can only get from x,0 and x,3x. With go into a loop and none of them can go from 1,1.
So when target x or y is even, divide it until odd. Then check if it fit the end points.
If not, then x,y can go from x,x+y. Since x+y is even, so it can go to x,(x + y) / 2.
In this case, for x,y, since (x+y)/2 is smaller then y, and it is possibly to be even again and keep divide 2. So finally it will either go to end with x = y case or it will go to x = 1 case.
