# Approach
- Create a new user defined function called helper that will do all the setting up of the next.pointers
- In the helper function, define a queue and an arraylist named q and child array respectively.
- The progression through each level will be simple, that is --> Take the root node, pass it in the queue and while the queue is not empty, empty out the whole level as you check for children of each node you remove.
- Append the children in the child array and connect all the next pointers in the child array to the other one with a new user defined function called convert.
- Add all the left and right nodes if they exist to the queue.
- Voila, all the next connections are done.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n)

- Space complexity: O(n)

